HEADWORD: Taffy
<hw>Taf"fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>taffy</ets> toffy.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of candy made of
molasses or brown sugar boiled down and poured out in shallow
pans.</def> <altsp>[Written also, in England,
<asp>toffy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Flattery; soft phrases.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

